{"TopicId":204099,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to lock robotic parts","CreatedByName":"sreinmann","CreatedById":110583,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-29T21:06:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sreinmann","CreatedById":110583,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-29T21:06:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have built a space station with robotic hinges, pistons, and servos to extend and position solar panel trusses (and other parts)\u00A0that were stowed for launch (and future travel). \u00A0However the parts continue to flex and migrate from their set position and I\u2019m worried about Krackeneffects.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow can I lock robotic parts and once locked can they be unwelded to restore later?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-10T05:13:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224011938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627592782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sreinmann\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/29/2021 at 11:06 PM, sreinmann said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow can I lock robotic parts and once locked can they be unwelded to restore later?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight-clicking on the robotic part brings up the Part Action Window (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E). You have to look carefully, cause there are a lot of buttons and sliders, but one of the buttons is labeled \u0027locked\u0027, and will toggle between locked and unlocked state.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBear in mind that there is a known bug with robotics parts slowly drifting off their locked state, apparently when starting/stopping time warp near the craft (not sure if also when loading a craft). Locking doesn\u0027t help this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maddog59","CreatedById":205063,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-16T18:30:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224011938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627592782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sreinmann\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/29/2021 at 3:06 PM, sreinmann said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow can I lock robotic parts and once locked can they be unwelded to restore later?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may want to consider creating one or more action groups that include the \u0027Toggle Lock\u0027 function for each of the parts of interest. That way, if you come back to the station and find that they\u0027ve unlocked (per \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152460\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@swjr-swis\u003C/a\u003E\u0027 answer), you can easily re-lock them.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ave369","CreatedById":174958,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-08T11:42:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI prefer to strut them fast. After the station is deployed, these struts can be recovered by an engineer and re-used to fix the station\u0027s final shape and prevent noodling.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"khafhji","CreatedById":224741,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-10T02:33:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224017419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628572437\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/10/2021 at 12:13 AM, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut one of the buttons is labeled \u0027locked\u0027,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont see that button\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-10T17:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224217460\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221673318000\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224741\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022khafhji\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, khafhji said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont see that button\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuick-slapped four different robotics parts on a pod to test. The locked button is in the red squares:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228JgPZSI.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/8JgPZSI.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may need to enable \u0027advanced tweakables\u0027 in your game settings to see them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}